com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom
Enum JSOM.JSOMType

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<JSOM.JSOMType>
      com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.JSOM.JSOMType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<JSOM.JSOMType>
Enclosing interface:
JSOM
public static enum JSOM.JSOMType
extends java.lang.Enum<JSOM.JSOMType>

Defines constants for all non-abstract JSOM types, excepting those types derived from Expression (which is the base type for all kind of expression types) and StatementBlockElement (which is the base type for all kind of statements).

From a JSOMType's view all Expression types and StatementBlockElement types are bound to the JSOMType EXPRESSION and STATEMENT_BLOCK_ELEMENT respectively.

The constant names correspond to the appropriate JSOM subtype class names.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

QUALIFIED_IDENTIFIER

public static final JSOM.JSOMType QUALIFIED_IDENTIFIER
Constant for a JSOM type representing a qualified identifier.

Qualified identifier means that a certain identifier may be a qualified identifier. It is not obligatory that the identifier is acutally a qualified identifier, i.e. it may also be a single identifier.

See Also:
QualifiedIdentifier

STATEMENT_BLOCK_ELEMENT

public static final JSOM.JSOMType STATEMENT_BLOCK_ELEMENT
Constant for a JSOM type representing a statement block element.

A statement block element can be a local variable declaration, a local type declaration or any statement type. A more formal description of a statement block element is that such elements are direct children of a statement block scope (method or constructor bodies, compound statements, etc).

Note that this constant will be used for all JSOM types representing a statement block element. There are various subtypes of the type StatementBlockElement and it's up to the StatementBlockElement base type to define appropriate constants for the various statement block element types.

See Also:
StatementBlockElement
